<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>TorrentX — Privacy Policy</title>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&display=swap');

        :root {
            --bg: #0a0a0a;
            --surface: #111111;
            --text: #e0e0e0;
            --accent: #ffffff;
        }

        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        
        body {
            font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
            background: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.8;
            padding: 40px 20px;
            min-height: 100vh;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
            -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 860px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: var(--surface);
            border: 1px solid #222222;
            border-radius: 16px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        header {
            background: #000000;
            padding: 70px 40px 55px;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #222;
        }

        .logo {
            width: 92px;
            height: 92px;
            margin: 0 auto 24px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            border: 3px solid white;
            border-radius: 50%;
            overflow: hidden; /* Added to clip the image to the circle */
        }

        /* New rule added to handle the image scaling perfectly */
        .logo img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            object-fit: cover;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: white;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            letter-spacing: -0.5px;
        }

        .tagline {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #888;
            letter-spacing: 2.5px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        .content {
            padding: 55px 45px;
        }

        section {
            margin-bottom: 52px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: white;
            margin-bottom: 22px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 14px;
            letter-spacing: -0.3px;
        }

        h2 svg {
            width: 26px;
            height: 26px;
            stroke: white;
            fill: none;
            stroke-width: 2.2;
        }

        p, li {
            font-size: 16.5px;
            color: #cccccc;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 28px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        strong {
            color: #ffffff;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .highlight {
            background: #1a1a1a;
            padding: 26px;
            border-radius: 14px;
            border-left: 4px solid #ffffff;
            margin: 32px 0;
            font-weight: 500;
            font-style: italic;
            color: #eeeeee;
        }

        .last-updated {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 15px;
            color: #666;
            margin: 40px 0 20px;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        footer {
            background: #000;
            padding: 45px 40px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #777;
            border-top: 1px solid #222;
        }

        footer p {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #777;
        }

        footer p:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
            font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            font-size: 12px;
            letter-spacing: 1.5px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="logo">
                <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/eb/26/be/eb26beef0cae2d3ef128556e27d3e55f.jpg" alt="TorrentX Logo">
            </div>
            <h1>TorrentX</h1>
            <p class="tagline">Free • Ad-Free • Private • Powerful</p>
        </header>

        <div class="content">

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
                    Privacy Policy
                </h2>
                <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> May 22, 2026</p>
                <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 22, 2026</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <p>TorrentX is a completely free, open-source Android application that provides high-performance BitTorrent downloading and intelligent media downloading with a focus on privacy, speed, and simplicity.</p>
                
                <div class="highlight">
                    We believe in radical transparency: <strong>TorrentX collects no personal identifying data</strong> and never sells your information. We only collect anonymous crash logs to ensure app stability.
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><path d="M14 2v6h6"/></svg>
                    1. What TorrentX Does
                </h2>
                <p>TorrentX offers full BitTorrent support using the powerful libtorrent4j engine, intelligent media downloading from popular platforms, automatic 4K/HDR muxing with FFmpeg, sequential downloading, background execution via WorkManager and Foreground Services, and advanced I/O optimization using Zero-Copy DirectByteBuffer technology.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
                    2. Anonymous Diagnostics & Crash Reporting
                </h2>
                <p>To ensure TorrentX runs smoothly and to help us quickly identify bugs in our native C++ engine, we utilize <strong>Google Firebase Crashlytics</strong>. If the app encounters a fatal error or crash, the following anonymous data is automatically collected:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Crash Logs & Stack Traces:</strong> Information detailing exactly which line of code caused the app to fail.</li>
                    <li><strong>Device Diagnostics:</strong> Non-identifying device states at the time of the crash, such as device model, OS version, orientation, and available RAM/storage.</li>
                    <li><strong>Installation UUID:</strong> A randomly generated, anonymous identifier used solely to count how many individual devices are affected by a specific bug.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This data is strictly utilized for analytics and stability improvements. It is encrypted in transit, processed securely on Google's servers, and is <strong>never</strong> used for advertising or cross-app tracking.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
                    3. Information We Do NOT Collect
                </h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>No names, emails, phone numbers, or any personal identifiers.</li>
                    <li>No advertising IDs or device fingerprinting.</li>
                    <li>No cloud accounts or login systems.</li>
                    <li>No browsing history or tracking of the files you download.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2.01 2.01 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2"/></svg>
                    4. Technical Information Processed Locally
                </h2>
                <p>The following information is handled <strong>only on your device</strong>:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Magnet links, .torrent files, and media URLs you manually add.</li>
                    <li>Peer-to-peer connections required by the BitTorrent protocol.</li>
                    <li>Download progress, resume data, and local settings stored in SQLite.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Your IP address may be visible to other peers and trackers as part of normal BitTorrent operation — this is unavoidable in any torrent client.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
                    5. Required Android Permissions & Their Purpose
                </h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>INTERNET</strong> — To connect to peers, trackers, and media servers.</li>
                    <li><strong>ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE</strong> — To enforce WiFi-Only mode.</li>
                    <li><strong>READ/WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE</strong> — To save downloaded files and read .torrent files.</li>
                    <li><strong>FOREGROUND_SERVICE</strong> — To keep downloads running in the background.</li>
                    <li><strong>POST_NOTIFICATIONS</strong> — To show download progress and status.</li>
                    <li><strong>WAKE_LOCK</strong> — To prevent the device from sleeping during active file writing.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/></svg>
                    6. Your Privacy Controls
                </h2>
                <p>You have complete control over your privacy:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>WiFi-Only mode, speed throttling, and battery saver.</li>
                    <li>Encryption modes and proxy support (SOCKS5, HTTP).</li>
                    <li>Port randomization and peer discovery controls.</li>
                    <li>Option to stop seeding at 100% to save bandwidth.</li>
                    <li>Full ability to delete all downloads and app data locally.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <div class="last-updated">
                This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. We recommend reviewing it periodically.<br>
                By using TorrentX, you agree to this policy.
            </div>
        </div>

        <footer>
            <p>TorrentX by AutcustDev — Built for users who value speed, simplicity, and privacy.</p>
            <p>Completely Free • No Ads • No Ad-Tracking • No Compromises</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
